---
// Outcomes band: bar chart comparing TMS vs alternatives
---

<section class="py-32 max-w-[1400px] mx-auto px-8">
  <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
    <!-- Left text -->
    <div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6" style="font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--muted);">
        <span style="width: 24px; height: 1px; background: rgba(10,22,40,0.3);"></span>
        <span>Outcomes &middot; Aggregate 2024&ndash;26</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="serif mb-8" style="font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 4.75rem); line-height: 0.95; color: var(--ink);">
        Data from<br/>
        <em>real patients,</em><br/>
        published quarterly.
      </h2>
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 28rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        Every verified clinic submits anonymized outcome data - response rates, remission at 6 weeks, and patient-reported QoL scores - in exchange for their listing. We publish a transparent aggregate.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
        <a href="#" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-5 py-3 border transition-all hover:!bg-[var(--ink)] hover:text-white hover:!border-[var(--ink)]"
           style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink); border: 1px solid var(--line); text-decoration: none;">
          Download Q1 2026 report
          <svg width="13" height="13" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path d="M12 3v12M8 11l4 4 4-4M3 15v4h18v-4"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a href="#" class="linky" style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted);">Methodology</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Right: bar chart card -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border" style="border-color: var(--line);">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-6 pb-6 border-b" style="border-color: var(--line);">
        <div>
          <div style="font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">Response rate</div>
          <div class="serif" style="font-size: 22px; color: var(--ink);">TMS vs alternatives (TRD cohort, n=4,102)</div>
        </div>
        <div style="font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted);">at 6 weeks post-treatment</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bars -->
      <div class="space-y-5">
        {[
          { name: 'TMS (iTBS)', value: 68, color: 'var(--ink)', note: '6 weeks &middot; 36 sessions' },
          { name: 'TMS (SAINT)', value: 79, color: 'var(--accent)', note: '5 days &middot; 50 sessions' },
          { name: 'SSRI (single trial)', value: 34, color: '#A4B0C8', note: 'STAR*D level 1 data' },
          { name: 'SSRI (after 2 trials)', value: 16, color: '#CBD2DD', note: 'STAR*D level 3 data' },
          { name: 'ECT', value: 74, color: 'var(--warm)', note: 'Inpatient cohort' },
        ].map((row) => (
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2 flex-wrap gap-1">
              <div style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500;">{row.name}</div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <span class="tabular-nums serif" style="font-size: 24px; color: var(--ink);">{row.value}<span style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted);">%</span></span>
                <span class="hidden sm:inline" style="font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted);">&middot; {row.note}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-2.5 rounded-full overflow-hidden" style="background: var(--paper2);">
              <div
                class="h-full rounded-full transition-all duration-1000"
                style={`width: ${row.value}%; background: ${row.color};`}
              ></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color: var(--line); font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6;">
        Sources: TMS List aggregate outcomes 2024&ndash;26 (n=4,102); Sheehan et al. 2017 (STAR*D re-analysis); Cole et al. 2020 (SAINT Stanford); Kellner et al. 2017 (ECT).
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .serif { font-family: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .linky { position: relative; }
  .linky:hover::after { transform: scaleX(1); }
  .linky::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -1px;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 1px;
    background: currentColor;
    transform: scaleX(0);
    transform-origin: left;
    transition: transform 0.35s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.8, 0.2, 1);
  }
</style>